\section install_ustk Installation

UsTk is a multi platform library that works under Linux, OSX and Windows, so to install UsTK you need the CMake configuration tool available from http://www.cmake.org. As UsTK is a set of modules for ViSP library, you will need to download it <a href="https://github.com/lagadic/visp" target="_parent">here</a>. Furthermore, depending on your operation system and the capabilities you need, you may install third party libraries listed <a href="https://github.com/lagadic/ustk/blob/master/README.md#dependencies" target="_parent">here</a>.

UsTK full installation procedure using CMake is detailed in the Installation from prebuild SDK tutorials and Installation from source tutorials. Getting started tutorials and documents in pdf are also available from https://visp.inria.fr/publications.

